Sentencas: Ferritic stainless steels currently used as the interconnect materials in solid oxide fuel cells do not exhibit adequate electronic conductivity over expected periods of service.
Titulo: Metal-Oxide Scale Interfacial Imperfections and Performance of Stainless Steels Utilized as Interconnects in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In addition to the relatively poor conductivity of the oxide scales, the metal-oxide scale interfacial defects contribute to significant conductivity losses.
Titulo: Metal-Oxide Scale Interfacial Imperfections and Performance of Stainless Steels Utilized as Interconnects in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In this work, the metal-oxide scale interfacial defects are studied for two grades of stainless steels, AISI-SAE 430 and ZMG232.
Titulo: Metal-Oxide Scale Interfacial Imperfections and Performance of Stainless Steels Utilized as Interconnects in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Scanning electron microscopy, as well as surface science analysis techniques including Auger electron spectroscopy, X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy, and secondary-ion mass spectroscopy, was used to study the metal-oxide scale interface for AISI-SAE 430 and for ZMG232 coupons.
Titulo: Metal-Oxide Scale Interfacial Imperfections and Performance of Stainless Steels Utilized as Interconnects in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Oxide scale spallation occurred during rapid cooling of oxidized AISI-SAE 430 steels.
Titulo: Metal-Oxide Scale Interfacial Imperfections and Performance of Stainless Steels Utilized as Interconnects in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Large, micrometer-sized cavities appeared beneath the spalled scales on AISI-SAE 430.
Titulo: Metal-Oxide Scale Interfacial Imperfections and Performance of Stainless Steels Utilized as Interconnects in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The metal substrate is not in contact with the scale in these locations.
Titulo: Metal-Oxide Scale Interfacial Imperfections and Performance of Stainless Steels Utilized as Interconnects in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Moreover, for this steel, nonmetallic and metallic impurities, such as Si, S, Cl, N, F, Pb, V, and Al, segregate at the metal-oxide scale interface and result in reduced metal-to-scale adhesion and contact area.
Titulo: Metal-Oxide Scale Interfacial Imperfections and Performance of Stainless Steels Utilized as Interconnects in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: However, no marked impurity segregation and spallation occur for ZMG232, which contains Zr and La as reactive elements that prevent impurity segregation.
Titulo: Metal-Oxide Scale Interfacial Imperfections and Performance of Stainless Steels Utilized as Interconnects in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
